<TITLE> DU admission exams start Nov 6 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 22 (bdnews24.com)Dhaka University will hold its first year honours admission exams for the academic year 2009-2010 will be held from Nov 6 to Dec 11, officials said Sunday. Applicants will be able to collect and submit admission forms from Oct 1 to Oct 19. Vice chancellor AAMS Arefin Siddik told bdnews24.com that the dates were fixed on Saturday. This year for the first time the DU authority will also administer admission tests for private medical colleges under a new 'Ma unit'. Previously the exams were held by the individual college authorities. Admission exams for the Institute of Fine Arts will also be held by DU under the 'Cha unit'. An official from the university's public relations department told bdnews24.com the exam for 'Kha' (arts faculty) and 'Ma' (private medical colleges) units will be held on Nov 6. Exams for 'Ka' (science faculty), 'Ga' (business), 'Gha' (social science) and 'Cha' (fine arts) units will be held on Nov 13, Nov 20, Dec 4 and Dec 11 respectively. Applicants will need a combined GPA 7 in SSC and HSC exams to apply for 'Kha unit'. For 'Ka', 'Ga' and 'Cha' the required combined GPA in SSC and HSC is 8, 7.5 and 6 respectively. The minimum GPA requirement for Gha unit, which enables students to change their group, will be according to their background; for an applicant from humanities will need GPA 7, as required for Kha unit; an applicant from science will need GPA 8. bdnews24
